Email Change Request - Email
custom_preconds:
GIVEN a user is logged in
AND on the Profile Page (/account)
AND on the General Account Settings
custom_steps:
When a user clicks on the Contact section
AND updates the email address
custom_expected:
THEN a MLB account email address change email is received

From - info@mail.mlblists.com
Subject - MLB account email address change
Body - contains MLB logo, confirmation button (Confirm Email Change), text about link expiration (1 hour), text about the new email address, Contact Us link to the Customer Service page

title: Email Change Request - Success
custom_preconds: GIVEN a user submitted an email change request
custom_steps: WHEN a user clicks on the Confirm Email Change button
custom_expected:
THEN the user will be linked to the Profile
AND the email will be changed

title: Email Change Request - Old Email Login
custom_preconds: GIVEN a user confirmed a email change request
custom_steps:
WHEN a user is on the login page (/login)
AND logs in with the old email and password
custom_expected:
THEN the user will not be able to login
AND the user will see Authentication Error

title: Email Change Request - New Email Login
custom_preconds: GIVEN a user confirmed a email change request
custom_steps:
WHEN a user is on the login page (/login)
AND logs in with the new email and password
custom_expected: THEN the user will be able to login

title: Email Change Request - Expiration
custom_preconds:
GIVEN a user submitted an email change request
AND waits for the link in the email to expire
custom_steps: WHEN a user clicks on the Confirm Email Change button
custom_expected:
THEN the user will be linked to the Error Page
AND the email will not be changed

Beta - https://beta-aws.mlb.com/help/expired-change-email
Prod - https://www.mlb.com/help/expired-change-email

title: Email Change Request - Multiple Requests
custom_preconds:
GIVEN a user is logged in
AND on the Profile Page (/account)
AND on the General Account Settings
custom_steps:
When a user clicks on the Contact
AND updates the email address with one request
AND updates the email address with a second request
AND updates the email address with a third request
custom_expected: THEN a MLB account email address change email is received for each request

title: Email Change Request - Multiple Requests Confirmation
custom_preconds: GIVEN a user submitted multiple email change requests
custom_steps:
WHEN a user clicks on one confirmation link
AND attempts to click on confirmation link for another request
custom_expected:
THEN the user will be linked to the Error Page
AND the email will not be changed

Beta - https://beta-aws.mlb.com/help/expired-change-email
Prod - https://www.mlb.com/help/expired-change-email

title: Email Change Request - Duplicate Emails
custom_preconds:
GIVEN an email A submits a email change request for email 1
AND the request is still pending
custom_steps: WHEN an email B submits a email change for request for email 1
custom_expected:
THEN a request is pending for email A and email B
AND when email A clicks to confirms email 1 request it is processed
AND email A is directed to the Account Profile page
AND when email B clicks to confirm email 1 request it is not processed 
AND email B is directed to error page

title: Email Change Request - Feature Flag
custom_preconds:
GIVEN a Dev has set the feature flag to off

lineup.profile.email-change-request.enabled = false
custom_steps: WHEN a user changes the email on the Profile
custom_expected:
THEN the email change request will be made without confirmation
AND no change request is sent

title: Email Change Request - DSS Cutover Flag enabled
custom_preconds: GIVEN a Dev has set the dssCutover flag to enabled
custom_steps: WHEN a user changes the email on the Profile
custom_expected:
THEN the email change request will be made with confirmation
AND when the user clicks on the confirmation link
AND the email is changed to the new email

title: Email Change Request - DSS Cutover Flag disabled
custom_preconds: GIVEN a Dev has set the dssCutover flag to disabled
custom_steps: WHEN a user changes the email on the Profile
custom_expected:
THEN the email change request will be made with confirmation
AND when the user clicks on the confirmation link
AND the email is changed to the new email

title: Health and Sanity Check on Profile Service Email Change - ENGAGE-3690 - Step 1 - 400 Status Code  for Duplicate Email
custom_preconds: GIVEN a user sends a request to /api/v1/email endpoint
custom_steps: WHEN a user passes an existing email that is already associated to an account
custom_expected:
THEN the user sees a 400 Bad Request from the Service
AND response message "Cannot update email, email <email> was taken"

title: Health and Sanity Check on Profile Service Email Change - ENGAGE-3690 - Step 2 -  400 Status Code Error for Duplicate Email (Different Case)
custom_preconds: GIVEN a user sends a request to /api/v1/email endpoint
custom_steps:
WHEN a user passes an existing email that is already associated to an account
AND the email is in different case (all uppercase for example)
custom_expected:
THEN the user sees a 400 Bad Request from the Service
AND response message "Cannot update email, email <email> was taken"

title: Health and Sanity Check for Profile Service Email Change - ENGAGE-3690 - Step 3 - 401 Status Code Error without Access Token
custom_preconds: GIVEN a user sends a request to /api/v1/email endpoint
custom_steps: WHEN a user attempts to change email without an access token in the Authorization Token
custom_expected: THEN the user sees a 401 Unauthorized response from the Service

title: Health and Sanity Check for Profile Service Email Change - ENGAGE-3690 - Step 4 -  400 Status Code Error with Non-email
custom_preconds: GIVEN a user sends a request to /api/v1/email endpoint
custom_steps: WHEN a user attempts to pass an invalid email to the service
custom_expected: THEN the user sees a 400 Bad Request response from the Service

title: Health and Sanity Check for Profile Service Email Change - ENGAGE-3690 - Step 5 -  400 Error with Bad Request
custom_preconds: GIVEN a user sends a request to /api/v1/email endpoint
custom_steps: WHEN a user attempts to pass a bad payload of data
custom_expected: THEN the user sees a 400 Bad Request response from the Service
